<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Identify a debugger for &quot;tuning&quot; the debug info.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The &quot;debugger tuning&quot; concept allows us to present a more intuitive</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// interface that unpacks into different sets of defaults for the various</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// individual feature-flag settings, that suit the preferences of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// various debuggers.  However, it&#39;s worth remembering that debuggers are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// not the only consumers of debug info, and some variations in DWARF might</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   of the target, that&#39;s a tuning decision;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// o if the feature is useful (or not) on a particular platform, regardless</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   of the debugger, that&#39;s a target decision.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// It&#39;s not impossible to see both factors in some specific case.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
